WEBVTT

00:00.007 --> 00:01.090
The Espheni power core,

00:01.114 --> 00:03.093
was never on Earth
in the first place.

00:03.117 --> 00:05.082
Previously on
<i>Falling Skies...</i>

00:05.194 --> 00:06.767
We're gonna have to figure out
a way to get up there,

00:07.006 --> 00:08.273
blow that
son of a bitch up.

00:08.297 --> 00:10.440
The Beamer will lock onto
the Espheni homing beacon

00:10.464 --> 00:12.091
and fly to the Moon base.

00:12.115 --> 00:13.435
That Beamer's
on a one-way ticket.

00:13.441 --> 00:14.414
I should've known...

00:14.438 --> 00:16.700
When they announced the draw,
you'd find a way to go.

00:16.724 --> 00:18.011
We don't know
what we don't know.

00:18.035 --> 00:20.498
Maybe Lexi will come back.
Maybe she's not too far gone.

00:20.522 --> 00:22.675
<i>You won't be able</i>
<i>to control her for much longer.</i>

00:24.134 --> 00:24.920
Something's coming.

00:24.944 --> 00:25.954
Beamers!

00:28.661 --> 00:29.827
Hello, father.

00:32.362 --> 00:34.430
Lexi?

00:34.464 --> 00:35.745
What the hell
are you doing here?

00:35.769 --> 00:36.895
I came back to talk to you.

00:36.963 --> 00:38.897
There is so much
I need to explain.

00:40.633 --> 00:42.500
Everybody, get back to cover!
Dad.

00:42.535 --> 00:44.695
For all we know, the Espheni
could be right behind her.

00:44.719 --> 00:46.571
Roger that.
Positions, everybody!

00:46.606 --> 00:48.006
What the hell you doing,
Mason?

00:48.040 --> 00:49.880
Take it easy, Pope.
I'll handle this situation.

00:49.904 --> 00:51.076
Y-you'll handle it?

00:51.110 --> 00:52.611
Two weeks ago,
we were 200 strong.

00:52.678 --> 00:53.845
We're now down
to about 20.

00:53.879 --> 00:56.615
And she's
the one responsible.

00:56.649 --> 00:58.416
We back off...

00:58.451 --> 01:01.486
Until he's had a chance
to gauge if she's a threat.

01:01.520 --> 01:03.955
If?!

01:04.022 --> 01:05.489
You gonna talk to her?

01:05.524 --> 01:07.058
How about put
her down...

01:07.126 --> 01:09.794
Before she takes us
all out?

01:13.432 --> 01:15.192
Make sure that he doesn't do
anything stupid.

01:15.226 --> 01:17.107
Mission impossible.
Be careful, the both of you.

01:17.130 --> 01:17.919
Yeah, yeah.

01:17.921 --> 01:19.771
It's so good
to see you both. I...

01:19.805 --> 01:23.642
I came to apologize,
to tell you you were right.

01:23.676 --> 01:26.678
Trusting the Espheni
was a terrible mistake.

01:26.712 --> 01:27.912
That's quite
an understatement.

01:27.936 --> 01:31.383
Your eyes --
they're different.

01:31.450 --> 01:33.585
They're the way they were
before the cocoon.

01:33.653 --> 01:35.654
And I can see clearly now.

01:35.688 --> 01:38.089
For the first time, I know
what I need to do.

01:38.124 --> 01:41.559
The Espheni are monsters.

01:41.594 --> 01:43.361
I want to help you
destroy them.

01:43.396 --> 01:44.696
Yeah, well, it's not
that simple.

01:44.730 --> 01:46.331
You left us to join them,

01:46.365 --> 01:48.466
you said they were your family,
you killed Lourdes --

01:48.501 --> 01:50.902
And there isn't a moment that
I'm not sick over what I did.

01:50.936 --> 01:53.805
Look, when I first came out of
the cocoon, I was so confused.

01:53.839 --> 01:56.107
I thought
I was helping Lourdes,

01:56.142 --> 01:58.502
freeing her from the pain she'd
suffer when the attack came.

01:58.537 --> 02:00.217
This isn't just about her.
Look around you.

02:00.241 --> 02:01.880
We were devastated
by that attack!

02:01.914 --> 02:04.049
Those of us who survived
hold you responsible.

02:04.083 --> 02:08.186
I am, so, please, please,
let me make it up to you.

02:10.656 --> 02:12.457
What do you think
you're doing?

02:12.491 --> 02:14.659
What Mason doesn't have
the guts to do himself.

02:14.694 --> 02:16.661
You're gonna put that rifle down,
or I'm gonna take it from you.

02:16.696 --> 02:17.976
Look, in case
you hadn't noticed,

02:18.000 --> 02:19.164
that is the enemy
over there.

02:19.198 --> 02:22.100
The Espheni plan to use me
as their weapon.

02:22.134 --> 02:26.004
Let me be <i>your</i> weapon
and end this war.

02:26.038 --> 02:28.673
How, Lexi?

02:28.708 --> 02:30.742
How can we let you back
into our lives?

02:30.776 --> 02:31.776
We can't.

02:33.813 --> 02:35.313
We can't.

02:35.347 --> 02:37.482
Damn it, Colonel, those soldiers
in the 2nd Mass --

02:37.516 --> 02:39.516
we may not have started out
as the best of friends,

02:39.540 --> 02:41.653
but I fought alongside
those people.

02:41.687 --> 02:44.322
I suffered with them in
that godforsaken ghetto, and for what?

02:44.390 --> 02:47.559
So that crazy, psycho alien bitch
could wipe them out? Unh-unh.

02:47.593 --> 02:48.960
When you came out
of that thing, I made a promise

02:48.994 --> 02:50.994
that I would stop you
if you tried to hurt anybody,

02:51.018 --> 02:52.464
and I didn't do it.

02:52.498 --> 02:55.033
I'm not making
that mistake again.

02:56.267 --> 02:59.269
You're not thinking clearly.
This is complicated.

02:59.304 --> 03:02.410
What's complicated about
the graves I dug, Colonel --

03:02.411 --> 03:04.378
the women and children
I put in the ground?

03:04.413 --> 03:05.713
I understand that.

03:05.747 --> 03:09.116
Let's just take it easy.
Come for a walk with me.

03:09.151 --> 03:10.584
Come on.

03:10.619 --> 03:14.088
[ Sighs, muttering ]

03:14.122 --> 03:15.523
I'm sorry, Cap.

03:15.557 --> 03:16.657
[ Grunts ]
Son of a...

03:18.326 --> 03:20.327
Hey, Pope! Don't do it!

03:23.231 --> 03:24.832
Pope, don't do it!
[ Gunshot ]

03:24.866 --> 03:25.833
Anne: [ Screams ]

